<P>And if any Clerk of a County-court &s;hall exact and take greater &s;ums for any Fee then is here, or in the Printed Book, or by any other Law &s;et down and e&s;tabli&s;hed, and &s;hall be legally convict thereof,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Penalty of Clerks exact|ing greater fees than is here appointed.</NOTE> &s;uch Per&s;on &s;o offending &s;hall forfeit for every pound of <HI>Tobacco</HI> &s;o exacted and taken, ten pounds of like, to the Per&s;on or Per&s;ons &s;o overcharged, to be Recovered by Action of Debt; any Law, Cu&s;tom, or U&s;age, to the contrary notwith|&s;tanding.</P>
